programme.title: Turf Life - A Day on the Bog
programme.desc: At Lough Boora Bog in Co Offaly, Derek Mooney and Sinead Kennedy examine the current uses of Irish bogs as well as their future potential in helping fight climate change. Bogs have been a vital source of fuel and sustenance for Ireland's people for millennia, but there has been growing recognition in recent times that human exploitation of them has brought many species of plants and animals to the brink of extinction. The vital role that bogs play in preventing flooding will also be examined(c)

Annabelle
programme.desc: A group of orphaned girls are taken in by a doll maker and his wife, who are still grieving the death of their daughter. However, they are soon terrorized by a haunted doll that's lurking within the couple's house

programme.title: The Dark Knight
programme.desc: In this intense sequel, Batman and idealistic district attorney Harvey Dent join forces to arrest and prosecute Gotham City's crime lords. But the deranged Joker raises the stakes by declaring all-out war on the forces of law and order

programme.title: Speed
programme.desc: Keanu Reeves plays Jack Traven, a young cop working with the LAPD bomb squad. Thwarting mad bomber Howard Payne, who has wired up a lift to explode, Traven finds himself the object of revenge. Payne rigs a bomb to a bus which arms when the speed reaches above 50mph and explodes if it drops beneath. With passenger Annie Porter drafted in to replace the injured driver, Traven has to work out how to disarm the bomb and evacuate the passengers while she keeps the bus up to speed in urban LA. Jan de Bont's thriller piles on the action and even after Traven saves everyone on the bus, there's still a roller-coaster finale on a runaway subway train commandeered by Payne

programme.title: Hard Candy
programme.desc: A 14-year-old girl (Ellen Page) and a thirtysomething photographer (Patrick Wilson) connect in an on-line chat room and arrange a meeting in this creepily provocative psychodrama that turns into an unsettling tale of retribution. Sandra Oh, Jennifer Holmes. Directed by David Slade

programme.title: The Human Stain
programme.desc: Well-acted but superficial adaptation of Philip Roth's novel about a light-skinned black college professor (Anthony Hopkins) who has been passing as white. Nicole Kidman, Ed Harris, Gary Sinise. Robert Benton directed

programme.title: El Cantante
programme.desc: A great soundtrack spices up this profile of pioneering Latino salsa singer Hector Lavoe, who was popular in the 1960s, '70s and '80s. Marc Anthony stars as Lavoe and his at-the-time-wife, Jennifer Lopez, produced and costars as his spouse

programme.title: Rabbit Hole
programme.desc: Becca (Nicole Kidman) and her husband Howie (Aaron Eckhart) mourn the death of their 4-year-old son, who was hit by a car while chasing the family dog into the street. The couple attend group therapy, where Howie befriends another woman. Meanwhile, Becca forms a tentative friendship with the teenager who accidentally killed her son. Directed by John Cameron Mitchell

programme.title: Cape Fear
programme.desc: Taut thriller about a sadistic psychopath, released from prison after serving a 14-year sentence, who is obsessed with taking his revenge on the lawyer who unsuccessfully defended him. Too clever to attack his victim directly, the devious ex-con begins a reign of terror that threatens the lawyer's whole family and causes underlying tensions to explode with devastating results. Remake of the 1962 thriller

programme.title: U.S. Marshals
programme.desc: United States Marshall Sam Gerard has been assigned to escort a federal prisoner to a maximum security prison in Missouri. On the same flight is Mark Sheridan, who has been arrested and charged with the murders of two Federal agents, though he insists he's innocent. The plane is involved in an accident leading to a crash, and after helping to rescue some of the passengers, Sheridan escapes

programme.title: The Rookie
programme.desc: A grizzled older cop is removed from a car theft case and partnered with a younger detective, but that doesn't stop him from interfering with the investigation, leaving his new partner stuck in between doing what's right and doing his job

programme.title: The Fugitive
programme.desc: Academy Award nominee Harrison Ford stars as the wrongly convicted Dr. Richard Kimble, and Academy Award winner Tommy Lee Jones is U.S. Marshal Sam Gerard, his relentless pursuer, in this all-time classic intense thriller based on the hit television series of the 1960s, The Fugitive. Kimble had the perfect life - a beautiful wife, medical career, an expensive townhouse - a perfect life until the night his wife was murdered, died in his arms and he was convicted of the crime. On his way to the penitentiary, Kimble escapes. Now, like hunted prey, he keeps running, determined only to find his wife's murderer. Caught in a nightmare from which he cannot awaken, Dr. Richard Kimble is the fugitive

programme.title: Indian Summer
programme.desc: Ensemble tale about friends who reunite at a camp that's in danger of closing down. Alan Arkin, Matt Craven. Beth: Diane Lane. Belston: Bill Paxton. Jennifer: Elizabeth Perkins. Brad: Kevin Pollak. Stick Coder: Sam Raimi. Matthew: Vincent Spano. Written and directed by Mike Binder

programme.title: Neighbors 2
programme.desc: Young parents Mac and Kelly find that their neighbour troubles are far from over when a hedonistic sorority moves in next door just as they're about to sell their house. During their feud with the ladies, the couple team up with ex-fratboy Teddy, who tormented them the last time around

programme.title: The Royal Tenenbaums
programme.desc: Offbeat comedy about a successful attorney who returns to the embittered and dysfunctional family he abandoned, claiming to have only six weeks to live. His sincere desire for forgiveness soon begins to have a profound effect upon the tortured and eccentric Tenenbaum clan

programme.title: Four Christmases
programme.desc: When their annual vacation getaway falls through, a happily unmarried couple are forced to spend Christmas with the families of their four divorced parents on the same day

programme.title: La La Land
programme.desc: Struggling actress Mia and aspiring jazz pianist Sebastian begin a whirlwind romance as they both pursue their dreams in Los Angeles. However, their blossoming relationship is challenged when their careers pull them in different directions

programme.title: The Bodyguard
programme.desc: Kevin Costner as an ex-Secret Service agent who falls for the pop diva (Whitney Houston) he's hired to protect. Despite the farfetched premise, the movie was a hit with audiences. The splendid soundtrack includes the hit song "I Will Always Love You." Written by Lawrence Kasdan, who penned the script in 1975 as a vehicle for Steve McQueen. Costner co-produced

programme.title: Next Day Air
programme.desc: A drug shipment is sent to the wrong address, prompting a frantic race to recover the package before its contents are discovered. Brody (Mike Epps) and Guch (Wood Harris) have mistakenly received a package containing 10 kilos of cocaine. If they can just find a buyer, they'll be rich. Meanwhile, intended recipients Jesus and Chita attempt to track down the shipment before drug lord Bodego Diablo realizes it's missing. But Bodega already knows the score and he wants his drugs back

programme.title: Absolutely Fabulous
programme.desc: In this big-screen continuation of the popular British sitcom, hard-living ladies Edina and Patsy flee to the French Riviera after an incident at a fashionable event causes them to be hounded by the paparazzi

programme.title: Mo' Better Blues
programme.desc: This ode to jazz focuses on Bleek Gilliam, a self-absorbed, contemporary trumpet player whose blind devotion to his own talent causes rifts in his professional and personal lives

programme.title: Lucky You
programme.desc: An aspiring lounge singer falls for a poker-playing stud in Las Vegas

programme.title: Mike and Dave Need Wedding Dates
programme.desc: Two hard-partying ladies see a viral video in which unruly brothers plead for dates for their sister's wedding in Hawaii, and decide to pose as the angels they're looking for in order to score a free trip

programme.title: The Fabulous Baker Boys
programme.desc: Piano-playing brothers, one a prodigy, the other mediocre, meet a chanteuse who livens up their act but whose affair with one may break them up

programme.title: Hidden Figures
programme.desc: Three female African-American mathematicians provide crucial calculations for NASA's space race against the Soviets, all while dealing with the racist and sexist assumptions of their white co-workers

programme.title: Fargo
programme.desc: The Coen brothers' sly drama about a policewoman (Frances McDormand) who's trying to determine how several murders and a kidnapping are linked to an unassuming car salesman (William H. Macy). Showalter: Steve Buscemi. Grimsrud: Peter Stormare

programme.title: Along Came a Spider
programme.desc: After losing his partner in an out of control bust, forensic psychologist Dr. Alex Cross (Morgan Freeman) stops working and cannot forgive himself. But he¿s drawn back to work when a brilliant but remorseless psychopath who has landed a teaching position at an exclusive private school in Washington, D.C. abducts one of his students, the daughter of a senator. Ollie MacArthur, the detective investigating the case, has strong words for Jezzie Flannigan, the Secret Service agent who mistakenly let Megan slip through her fingers. But Dr. Cross seeks out Flannigan, who he believes might have a valuable insight into the case. Soon, they both come to the terrible realization that this crime only represents the tip of the iceberg for the ruthless criminal

programme.title: A Perfect World
programme.desc: A Texas lawman pursues an escaped convict who has kidnapped a young boy. Meanwhile, in their dash to the border, the convict and the boy form a father-son attachment

programme.title: The Alamo
programme.desc: With Dennis Quaid and Billy Bob Thornton in the cast, this historical drama features magnificent war scenes as it reconstructs the revolution over the independence of Texas, in 1836 –before, during and after the construction of the Alamo (a fort built by Spanish missionaries to catechize the natives). Texans and Tejanos (born in Mexico), led by William Travis, Davy Crockett (Thornton) and Jim Bowie, are besieged by an army commanded by Mexican dictator Antonio Lopez de Santa Ana. Later, however, the outcome of the battle of San Jacinto, under General Sam Houston (Dennis Quaid), is the defeat of the Santa Ana men, which finally leads to the independence of the state

programme.title: Fatal Attraction
programme.desc: Michael Douglas stars as the loving husband and father who has a fling with Glenn Close only to find that when he tries to distance himself from her, he's caught in the web of a manipulative and increasingly violent woman. Adrian Lyne's Oscar-winning drama isn't just a thriller but a film that explores fidelity, sexual mores and the role of career women in the 80s (and also gave the world the phrase 'bunny-boiler')

programme.title: Things to Do in Denver...When You're Dead

Reluctantly, Garcia and his gang agree to do the deed but things go horribly wrong and the Man consigns them to their fate - violent death at the hands of hitman Mr Shhh (a creepy Steve Buscemi). Gary Fleder's first feature is witty and stylish with enough twists to keep the plot driving along at speed

programme.title: A Knight's Tale
programme.desc: Inspired by The Canterbury Tales, as well as the story of Ulrich von Lichtenstein, this is the story of William, a young squire with a gift for jousting. After his master dies suddenly, the squire hits the road with his cohorts Roland and Wat. On the journey, they stumble across an unknown writer, Chaucer. William, lacking a proper pedigree, convinces Chaucer to forge genealogy documents that will pass him off as a knight. With his newly-minted history in hand, the young man sets out to prove himself a worthy knight at the country's jousting competition, and finds romance along the way

programme.title: Ferris Bueller's Day Off

programme.title: The Lord of the Rings
programme.desc: In the mythical Middle-earth, a fantastic, mysterious world inhabited by men, Hobbits, wizards, elves, dwarfs and Trolls, lives Frodo Baggins (Elijah Wood), a shy Hobbit who must accomplish a difficult mission to save his land's destiny. It all begins when Frodo receives a ring from his uncle Bilbo (Ian Holm) and wizard Gandalf (Ian McKellen) discovers it is the Unique Ring itself. This powerful ring has been conceived by Sauron, the dark Lord of Mordor (Sala Baker), and with it, it is possible to enslave the whole of the Middle-earth through the use of dark forces. To destroy the ring, Frodo must take it to a distant mountain in Mordor, a region controlled by the Master of Evil. Fortunately, he is accompanied by a group formed by Hobbits Sam (Sean Astin), Merry (Dominic Monaghan) and Pippin (Billy Boyd), as well as Gandalf, the human warriors Aragorn (Viggo Mortensen) and Boromir (Sean Bean), and elf Legolas (Orlando Bloom). Together they have to confront dangerous obstacles in a frightening world of mystery and darkness. This spectacular adaptation of J.R.R. Tolkien's epic trilogy was directed by Peter Jackson

Over the course of the next century the two immerse themselves in a series of major conflicts, right up to the Vietnam War, where they are recruited by Major Stryker to join Team X: a killing machine staffed by other mutants. Uncomfortable with the merciless, legally dubious methods the unit employs, Howlett leaves, seeking a quiet life. Over the course of the next few years, Howlett, now known as Logan, seems to have realised his dream, having settled down with his girlfriend Kayla. However, a violent, catastrophic incident turns Logan's world upside down, propelling him on a course that will result in confrontation with his former ally Creed, as well as Logan's final transmogrification into Wolverine. Also starring Ryan Reynolds, Taylor Kitsch and Will.i.am

It's all here: hilarious comedy, authentic songs, and genuine nostalgia. Underneath all of the drug-induced insanity - indeed, what really makes the film exceptional - is a deep understanding of youth, love, and the politics of high school. An unforgettable cinematic experience unlike any other. If you haven't seen it already, you're missing out

programme.title: Charlie's Angels
programme.desc: When computer whiz Eric Knox realises his prize voice-ID software has been stolen he approaches Charlie's detective agency. Charlie entrusts the assignment to his three Angels - Natalie, Dylan and Alex - who are a combination of brilliance and killer looks

programme.title: Legally Blonde
programme.desc: Romantic comedy in which a gorgeous but shallow West Coast girl enrols in a prestigious law school in order to win back her ex. The girl is dumped by her wealthy East Coast boyfriend when he heads to Harvard graduate school. Determined to win him back, she signs up at the same school, and defies scorn and ridicule by showing an unexpected flair for the law(n)

programme.title: Legion
programme.desc: The angel Michael helps protect a group of strangers in a diner when God decides to wipe out humanity. Michael informs them that they are the only ones who can convince the Almighty to spare the human race(n)

programme.title: 28 Days
programme.desc: Gwen Cummings (Sandra Bullock) is a journalist who is fond of alcohol, parties and night life. At her sister's wedding, Gwen gets drunk, takes off in a limousine and causes a car accident. In court she is sentenced to 28 days in a rehab center. At the beginning, Gwen cannot admit her addiction, but after meeting Eddie Boone (Viggo Mortensen), a baseball player under treatment, her attitude starts to change(n)

programme.title: Cast Away
programme.desc: Two-time Academy Award winner Tom Hanks delivers an outstanding performance in this excellent Oscar winning Drama. Chuck Noland is a Fed-Ex manager who demands that everything must be on time and travels the world to make sure punctuality is on top of everything else. He has a girlfriend, Kelly, with whom he is deeply in love with and family he hardly sees. When work intrudes on Christmas Eve, Chuck has a quick gift exchange in the car and kisses Kelly goodbye. He boards a delivery plane going overseas which gets caught in a horrendous storm and crashes into the Pacific. The sole survivor Chuck washes up on a remote island along with several Fed-Ex packages that he must use for supplies. With limited luxury, he adapts to the island over the course of 1,500 nights(n)
